    <h2>2. What we collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Request data:</strong> name, contact channel (WhatsApp, Telegram, email, phone), route, dates, passengers, special requests.</li>
      <li><strong>Documents for the transfer</strong> (only on international routes): passport data required for the border crossing. Transmitted only to border authorities.</li>
      <li><strong>Technical data:</strong> IP address, browser type, pages visited, time on site — via Google Analytics 4 (IP anonymized).</li>
      <li><strong>Cookies:</strong> stored language preference (localStorage) and analytics consent (cookie).</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Why we process it</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>To handle and execute the transfer request (contract performance, LGPD Art. 7, V).</li>
      <li>To communicate about the request and the trip (contract performance).</li>
      <li>Accounting, tax compliance, NF-e (legal obligation, LGPD Art. 7, II).</li>
      <li>Site improvement and analytics (legitimate interest or consent, LGPD Art. 7, IX / I).</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Legal basis</h2>
    <p>We process data on the basis of contract performance, legal obligation, legitimate interest and your consent. Consent can be withdrawn at any time by writing to <a href="mailto:{{ site.contacts.email }}">{{ site.contacts.email }}</a>.</p>

    <h2>5. Who we share data with</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>The assigned driver (name, contact, route — to execute the trip).</li>
      <li>Payment providers (Pix, bank, acquirer) — when needed.</li>
      <li>Accountants and Brazilian tax authorities (as required by law).</li>
      <li>Google (Google Analytics, subject to consent) — processes technical data.</li>
      <li>Border authorities on international routes — only data necessary for the crossing.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We do not sell your data to third parties for advertising purposes.</p>

    <h2>6. How long we keep data</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Request data — 5 years (Brazilian limitation period for services).</li>
      <li>Tax documents (NF-e etc.) — 5 years (Receita Federal requirement).</li>
      <li>Analytics cookies — up to 14 months (Google Analytics default).</li>
      <li>Marketing communications (if you opted in) — until consent is withdrawn.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>7. Your rights (LGPD Art. 18)</h2>
    <p>You have the right to: confirm processing, access your data, correct inaccuracies, delete data (where not prohibited by law), receive a portable copy, withdraw consent, learn who we share data with and lodge a complaint with the ANPD (Brazilian Data Protection Authority).</p>
    <p>Requests — to <a href="mailto:{{ site.contacts.email }}">{{ site.contacts.email }}</a>. Response within 15 days.</p>

